Git basic commands:

git clone: fully copy repo from remote
While in the git local directory run:
git pull: sync with remote repo
git status
git add -A: add all files that have changed
git commit -m "your message"
git commit: to enter multiple line comment
git push: push changes to remote server
git branch: show list of branches and highlight the active one
git branch new_feature: create a branch named new_feature. It will contain a clone of all files from master branch.
git checkout new_feature: switch to new branch working directory
git merge <branch name>: merge current branch with <branch name>
git log: show git log
git mv file new_file: rename a file or move it arround

To initialize an existing directory as git directory and then commit it to server:
cd existing_folder
git init
git remote add origin http://git-server/akaouris/example.git
git add -A
git commit -m "your comment"
git push -u origin master



